04/09/2006
SOFIA, Bulgaria -- Sofia Mayor Boyko Borissov announced plans on Sunday (3 September) to establish his own party. 
In an interview on the national TV channel bTV, Borissov said he would register a party on 3 December, based on the political movement he has established, Citizens for European Development of Bulgaria. 
He also stressed he has no interest in running in the 1 October presidential election.
Also Sunday, it was announced that Chief Prosecutor Boris Velchev is expected to submit a request to the High Judicial Council, regarding lifting the immunity of several more prosecutors, accused of various violations. 
His deputy says their names surfaced during an internal investigation Velchev had ordered. 
(Monitor, Sega - 04/09/06; bTV, Mediapool - 03/09/06)
